rComments: Incredibly helpful professor! Definitely accomodating with any problems. He speaks a lot clearer in the more specialized classes, and clarifies all the difficulties in the text.

His lectures were okay, but sometimes his accent and line of thinking were hard to understand at times. Let's be honest though, medieval philosophy just isn't that fun to begin with. He was a really sweet person though and always willing to help. The TA for that class saved my grade. She was amazing!

Lectures are organized and the overhead notes provided are useful when studying/preparing for essays and tests. He is exceptionally helpful as he will discuss questions, look over drafts, provide extra office hours and offer extensions. He certainly seems confident, does not mumble anymore. Marks tough but fair. Great professor overall!

Easy class.  His slides are awesome (although it irritated me because I felt like students who didn't bother to come to lectures got as much material from the slides as we got in class).  Very Euro-hot.  Accent at times frustrating.  Very willing to talk to students.  I'd take the class again.
Besides how he looks like he is so romantic, he is a great prof. Very helpful and he really wants you to learn the material. I love him.

Pickave gave me a greater appreciation for medieval Philosophy, a renewed interest in metaphysics, a new respect for philosophy professors (who are almost ALL socially awkward) and a humble criticism of my own beliefs and theories. He is intelligent, humble, patient and very handsome! Large classes aren't everyones forte. Great Prof!

I agree, the man is very attractive and that is perhaps the only motivation I have to attending his class (purely aesthetic). I can't say much for his lecturing style since I can barely make out what he is saying! And the slides? Useless. I am an auditory learner so I don't benefit at all. In his defense, there is a language barrier!
A little socially awkward but super nice, really helpful and encouraging, and just a great prof overall.

Pickave is a nice guy ("sort of," in that cold European kind of way), but his "lecturing" style tends to suck whatever joy there is to be had from the material. He doesn't lecture so much as he draws attention to difficult points in the reading material, sans adequate exposition. Very, very dry. His overheads are useless and distracting.

Yes, he seems a little nervous when lecturing, but knows his stuff. Much more confident one on one. Very thorough with the material. He cares about his students and is very patient with them. And my God is he hot! Maybe it's just me, but I could watch him lecture for an eternity. *GRRRIN*.

He needsto work on his public speaking.  The material covered is difficult to understand at times, and his muttering, as well as his awkwardness doesn't help. He could be a great professor if he had more confidence.

Yep, he mutters...I sit near the front and still can't hear half the things he say.    But you can do well as long as you read his slides and try to stay awake in class.  He really cares about his students, though--the only prof who knows half of his class's (>50 ppl) names.  He's very helpful and less muttery in person, you just have to ask.
accent may cause problems understanding the material..

Had to drop this course, I couldnt concentrate on what he was saying due to his accent, quiet voice, and tendency to mutter. The material itself wasnt too interesting, and wasnt made any clearer by the slides. That said, I didnt stick around long enough to find out how he marks, or if you even had to be awake to get a descent mark.

He's adorable, but it is hard to follow the theories because of his thick German accent, and also he mutters a fair bit. But he's very approachable, helpful, and encouraging. And funny. Great slides. I wish the class was more interactive; everyone seemed dead. The material is pretty great though, and you can tell he loves it too.

His english isn't perfect, so if you don't follow him word for word you won't get what he's saying. But his slides are incredible, they summarize everything so perfectly, so that you could pass without reading the required readings.
